ble Commonwealth country. No prior study/work for more than one year in a high-income country.', 'First degree of at least upper second-class (2:1) honours standard, or lower second-class with relevant postgraduate qualification (Master''s). Unable to afford study without scholarship. Must return to home country after scholarship. No prior study/work for more than one year in a high-income country.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Commonwealth Scholarship Commission in the UK (CSC) and participating UK universities, funded by UK Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) Application Deadline (general period): Applications for 2026/27 are closed. Universities nominate candidates to CSC in March 2026.', 'Master''s (full-time, 12 months, no undergraduate or PhD study)', 'High-quality postgraduate students from Least Developed and middle-income Commonwealth countries (Bangladesh, Belize, Botswana, Cameroon, Dominica, Eswatini, Fiji, Gabon, Ghana, Grenada, Guyana, India, Jamaica, Kenya, Kiribati, Lesotho, Malawi, Malaysia, Maldives, Mauritius, Montserrat, Mozambique, Namibia, Nauru, Nigeria, Pakistan, Papua New Guinea, Rwanda, Saint Helena, Saint Lucia, Saint Vincent and The Grenadines, Samoa, Sierra Leone, Solomon Islands, South Africa, Sri Lanka, Tanzania, The Gambia, Togo, Tonga, Tuvalu, Uganda, Vanuatu, Zambia). Must be permanently resident in an eligible Commonwealth country. No prior study/work for more than one year in a high-income country.', 'Approved airfare (CSC funded), full tuition fees (CSC and university funded), stipend (£1,452/month or £1,781/month for London - university funded), warm clothing allowance (university funded), thesis grant (university funded, CSC funded), study travel grant (university funded, CSC funded), TB test contribution (university funded, CSC funded), family allowances (child £622/month for first, £154/month for second/third for single parents).', 'Not specified.', 'First degree of at least upper second-class (2:1) honours standard, or lower second-class with relevant postgraduate qualification (Master''s). Unable to afford study without scholarship. Must return to home country after scholarship. No prior study/work for more than one year in a high-income country.', NULL, 'https://cscuk.fcdo.gov.uk/scholarships/commonwealth-shared-scholarships/', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'UK-based scholarships for developing country students', 'Commonwealth Distance Learning Master’s Scholarships', 'Commonwealth Scholarship Commission in the UK (CSC) and participating UK universities Application Deadline (general period): Applications for 2026/27 are closed. Universities nominate candidates to CSC in June 2026. Outcomes by August 2026.', NULL, 'https://cscuk.fcdo.gov.uk/scholarships/commonwealth-distance-learning-scholarships/', 'full_ride', 'Full tuition fees. Study grants where required. (No airfare or living stipend as it''s distance learning).', NULL, ARRAY['phd','master','bachelor']::text[], NULL, ARRAY['Bangladesh','Belize','Botswana','Cameroon','Dominica','Fiji','Ghana','Guyana','India','Jamaica','Kenya','Kiribati','Lesotho','Malawi','Malaysia','Maldives','Mauritius','Mozambique','Namibia','Nauru','Nigeria','Pakistan','Papua New Guinea','Rwanda','Samoa','Sierra Leone','Solomon Islands','South Africa','Sri Lanka','Tanzania','Gambia','Togo','Tonga','Tuvalu','Uganda','Vanuatu','Zambia']::text[], 'High-quality postgraduate students from least developed and middle-income Commonwealth countries (Bangladesh, Belize, Botswana, Cameroon, Dominica, Eswatini, Fiji, Gabon, Ghana, Grenada, Guyana, India, Jamaica, Kenya, Kiribati, Lesotho, Malawi, Malaysia, Maldives, Mauritius, Montserrat, Mozambique, Namibia, Nauru, Nigeria, Pakistan, Papua New Guinea, Rwanda, Saint Helena, Saint Lucia, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, Samoa, Sierra Leone, Solomon Islands, South Africa, Sri Lanka, Tanzania, The Gambia, Togo, Tonga, Tuvalu, Uganda, Vanuatu, Zambia). Must be permanently resident in a developing Commonwealth country.', 'First degree of at least upper second-class (2:1) standard, or lower qualification with sufficient relevant experience. Unable to afford study without scholarship. Must return to home country after scholarship.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Commonwealth Scholarship Commission in the UK (CSC) and participating UK universities Application Deadline (general period): Applications for 2026/27 are closed. Universities nominate candidates to CSC in June 2026. Outcomes by August 2026.', 'Master''s (distance learning only, no undergraduate or PhD study)', 'High-quality postgraduate students from least developed and middle-income Commonwealth countries (Bangladesh, Belize, Botswana, Cameroon, Dominica, Eswatini, Fiji, Gabon, Ghana, Grenada, Guyana, India, Jamaica, Kenya, Kiribati, Lesotho, Malawi, Malaysia, Maldives, Mauritius, Montserrat, Mozambique, Namibia, Nauru, Nigeria, Pakistan, Papua New Guinea, Rwanda, Saint Helena, Saint Lucia, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, Samoa, Sierra Leone, Solomon Islands, South Africa, Sri Lanka, Tanzania, The Gambia, Togo, Tonga, Tuvalu, Uganda, Vanuatu, Zambia). Must be permanently resident in a developing Commonwealth country.', 'Full tuition fees. Study grants where required. (No airfare or living stipend as it''s distance learning).', 'Not specified.', 'First degree of at least upper second-class (2:1) standard, or lower qualification with sufficient relevant experience. Unable to afford study without scholarship. Must return to home country after scholarship.', NULL, 'https://cscuk.fcdo.gov.uk/scholarships/commonwealth-distance-learning-scholarships/', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'UK-based scholarships for developing country students', 'Queen Elizabeth Commonwealth Scholarships (QECS)', 'Association of Commonwealth Universities (ACU), supported by The Commonwealth Scholarship and Fellowship Plan (CSFP) endowment fund. Application Deadline (general period): Cycle 1 opens November/December, Cycle 2 opens March/April. Applications for 2026/27 Cycle 2: Open 9 April 2026, Close 3 June 2026.', NULL, 'https://www.acu.ac.uk/funding-opportunities/for-students/scholarships/queen-elizabeth-commonwealth-scholarships/', 'tuition_only', 'Fully-funded tuition fees, living allowance (stipend), return economy flights to host country, one-off arrival allowance, research support grant (on request).', NULL, ARRAY['master']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Students from Commonwealth countries, committed to creating change in their communities. Scholarships are hosted in low or middle-income Commonwealth countries, not necessarily the UK.', 'Minimum of 2:1 or equivalent at undergraduate level. Must apply to an ACU member university in a low or middle-income Commonwealth country. Must apply for admission to the chosen university/course.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Association of Commonwealth Universities (ACU), supported by The Commonwealth Scholarship and Fellowship Plan (CSFP) endowment fund. Application Deadline (general period): Cycle 1 opens November/December, Cycle 2 opens March/April. Applications for 2026/27 Cycle 2: Open 9 April 2026, Close 3 June 2026.', 'Master''s (two-year master''s degree)', 'Students from Commonwealth countries, committed to creating change in their communities. Scholarships are hosted in low or middle-income Commonwealth countries, not necessarily the UK.', 'Fully-funded tuition fees, living allowance (stipend), return economy flights to host country, one-off arrival allowance, research support grant (on request).', 'Not specified.', 'Minimum of 2:1 or equivalent at undergraduate level. Must apply to an ACU member university in a low or middle-income Commonwealth country. Must apply for admission to the chosen university/course.', NULL, 'https://www.acu.ac.uk/funding-opportunities/for-students/scholarships/queen-elizabeth-commonwealth-scholarships/', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'DAAD Development-Related Postgraduate Courses (EPOS)', 'Germany / DAAD (German Academic Exchange Service)', 'Germany', 'https://www2.daad.de/deutschland/stipendium/datenbank/en/21148-scholarship-database/?status=&origin=&subjectGrps=&daad=&intention=&q=development&page=1&detail=50076777', 'stipend', 'Monthly payments (€992 for graduates, €1,300 for doctoral candidates, increasing to €1,400 from Feb 2026), health, accident, and personal liability insurance, travel allowance. Additional benefits may include rent subsidy and family allowance under certain circumstances.', 1061.44, ARRAY['phd','master']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Graduates with at least two years'' professional experience from developing and newly industrialized countries (refer to [DAC list of eligible countries](https://static.daad.de/media/daad_de/pdfs_nicht_barrierefrei/in-deutschland-studieren-forschen-lehren/dac_laenderliste_epos.pdf) [1]).', 'Bachelor''s degree (usually four-year course) in an appropriate subject with above-average results (upper third), at least two years of related professional experience after the first degree, development-related motivation, and language skills (B1 German for German-taught courses, adequate English for English-taught courses). Academic degrees should normally not be more than six years old. Applicants resident in Germany for longer than 15 months at the application deadline are not eligible.', NULL, 'varies', NULL, NULL, 'Germany / DAAD (German Academic Exchange Service)', 'Master''s, PhD (in exceptional cases)', 'Graduates with at least two years'' professional experience from developing and newly industrialized countries (refer to [DAC list of eligible countries](https://static.daad.de/media/daad_de/pdfs_nicht_barrierefrei/in-deutschland-studieren-forschen-lehren/dac_laenderliste_epos.pdf) [1]).', 'Monthly payments (€992 for graduates, €1,300 for doctoral candidates, increasing to €1,400 from Feb 2026), health, accident, and personal liability insurance, travel allowance. Additional benefits may include rent subsidy and family allowance under certain circumstances.', 'Not specified, but offered for various postgraduate courses.', 'Bachelor''s degree (usually four-year course) in an appropriate subject with above-average results (upper third), at least two years of related professional experience after the first degree, development-related motivation, and language skills (B1 German for German-taught courses, adequate English for English-taught courses). Academic degrees should normally not be more than six years old. Applicants resident in Germany for longer than 15 months at the application deadline are not eligible.', 'Varies by study program; generally between June and December for the following academic year (e.g., August-November 2025 for 2026/2027 intake) [2].', '[DAAD EPOS](https://www2.daad.de/deutschland/stipendium/datenbank/en/21148-scholarship-database/?status=&origin=&subjectGrps=&daad=&intention=&q=development&page=1&detail=50076777)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'DAAD Research Grants', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'stipend', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'Research Grants in Germany', 'Germany / DAAD (German Academic Exchange Service)', 'Germany', 'https://www2.daad.de/deutschland/stipendium/datenbank/en/21148-scholarship-database/?status=&origin=&subjectGrps=&daad=&intention=&q=research&page=1&detail=57742121', 'stipend', 'Monthly scholarship payments (€1,400), health, accident, and personal liability insurance, travel allowance. For funding periods over six months: research allowance (€460), rent subsidy, family allowance. Language course support also available.', 1498.0, ARRAY['phd']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Doctoral students and postdocs from universities or research institutions outside Germany.', 'Doctoral students: start of doctorate not more than 3 years ago. Postdocs: doctorate completed not more than 4 years ago. Research project at a state or state-recognised German university or non-university research institute with a scientific supervisor. Applicants resident in Germany for longer than 15 months at the application deadline are not eligible.', NULL, 'annual', NULL, NULL, 'Germany / DAAD (German Academic Exchange Service)', 'PhD students (research stays), Postdocs (early phase, up to 4 years after completing doctorate)', 'Doctoral students and postdocs from universities or research institutions outside Germany.', 'Monthly scholarship payments (€1,400), health, accident, and personal liability insurance, travel allowance. For funding periods over six months: research allowance (€460), rent subsidy, family allowance. Language course support also available.', 'Not specified.', 'Doctoral students: start of doctorate not more than 3 years ago. Postdocs: doctorate completed not more than 4 years ago. Research project at a state or state-recognised German university or non-university research institute with a scientific supervisor. Applicants resident in Germany for longer than 15 months at the application deadline are not eligible.', 'Annually updated in the second quarter, generally in the same period as the previous year [3].', '[DAAD Research Grants](https://www2.daad.de/deutschland/stipendium/datenbank/en/21148-scholarship-database/?status=&origin=&subjectGrps=&daad=&intention=&q=research&page=1&detail=57742121)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'KAAD Scholarship Programme 1 (Invitation Programme)', 'Germany / KAAD (Catholic Academic Exchange Service)', 'Germany', 'https://www.kaad.de/en/stipendien', 'stipend', 'Not explicitly detailed on the overview page, but generally aims to support studies/research stays.', NULL, ARRAY['master']::text[], NULL, ARRAY['Ethiopia','Ghana','Guatemala','Jordan','Kenya','Lebanon','Peru','Zimbabwe','Thailand','Myanmar','Syria']::text[], 'Postgraduates and professionals from focus countries (developing countries) in Africa, Asia, Latin America, Central, Southeastern, and Eastern Europe, and the Middle East. Specific In-country programs in Ethiopia, Ghana, Guatemala, Jordan, Kenya, Lebanon, Peru, Zimbabwe. Third-country programs for students from other continents at selected locations (e.g., Bangkok/Thailand for Myanmar students, refugees from Syria in Lebanon and Jordan).', 'Postgraduates and persons with proven professional experience. For In-country/Third-country programs, Master''s studies in the home country or a selected third country. Applicants must be nominated or invited.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Germany / KAAD (Catholic Academic Exchange Service)', 'Postgraduate studies, research stays (primarily for Germany); Master''s studies (In-country/Third-country programs).', 'Postgraduates and professionals from focus countries (developing countries) in Africa, Asia, Latin America, Central, Southeastern, and Eastern Europe, and the Middle East. Specific In-country programs in Ethiopia, Ghana, Guatemala, Jordan, Kenya, Lebanon, Peru, Zimbabwe. Third-country programs for students from other continents at selected locations (e.g., Bangkok/Thailand for Myanmar students, refugees from Syria in Lebanon and Jordan).', 'Not explicitly detailed on the overview page, but generally aims to support studies/research stays.', 'Not specified.', 'Postgraduates and persons with proven professional experience. For In-country/Third-country programs, Master''s studies in the home country or a selected third country. Applicants must be nominated or invited.', 'Not specified on the overview page; applicants should inquire directly.', '[KAAD Scholarships](https://www.kaad.de/en/stipendien)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'KAAD Scholarship Programme 2', 'Germany / KAAD (Catholic Academic Exchange Service)', 'Germany', 'https://www.kaad.de/en/stipendien', 'stipend', 'Not explicitly detailed on the overview page.', NULL, ARRAY['phd','master']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Students from countries of the Global South who are already studying for their PhD or Master''s degree in Germany.', 'Must be from a country of the Global South and already enrolled in a Master''s or PhD program in Germany. Applicants are proposed by Catholic University Chaplaincies.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Germany / KAAD (Catholic Academic Exchange Service)', 'Master''s, PhD', 'Students from countries of the Global South who are already studying for their PhD or Master''s degree in Germany.', 'Not explicitly detailed on the overview page.', 'Not specified.', 'Must be from a country of the Global South and already enrolled in a Master''s or PhD program in Germany. Applicants are proposed by Catholic University Chaplaincies.', 'Not specified on the overview page; applicants should inquire directly.', '[KAAD Scholarships](https://www.kaad.de/en/stipendien)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'NL Scholarship (formerly Holland Scholarship)', 'Netherlands / Dutch Ministry of Education, Culture and Science, and Dutch research universities/universities of applied sciences.', 'Netherlands', 'https://www.studyinnl.org/finances/nl-scholarship', 'full_ride', '€5,000 (one-time payment in the first year of studies). This is not a full-tuition scholarship.', 5350.0, ARRAY['master','bachelor']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'International students from outside the European Economic Area (EEA).', 'Non-EEA nationality, applying for a full-time bachelor''s or master''s program at a participating Dutch higher education institution, meeting specific institutional requirements, and not holding a degree from a Dutch education institution.', '2025-11-01'::date, 'fixed', NULL, NULL, 'Netherlands / Dutch Ministry of Education, Culture and Science, and Dutch research universities/universities of applied sciences.', 'Bachelor''s, Master''s', 'International students from outside the European Economic Area (EEA).', '€5,000 (one-time payment in the first year of studies). This is not a full-tuition scholarship.', '2,112 students per academic year (jointly granted by the Ministry and 47 Dutch higher education institutions) [4].', 'Non-EEA nationality, applying for a full-time bachelor''s or master''s program at a participating Dutch higher education institution, meeting specific institutional requirements, and not holding a degree from a Dutch education institution.', 'Application for the 2026-2027 academic year opened on November 1, 2025. Specific deadlines vary by institution; applicants must check the website of their chosen institution [4].', '[Study in NL - NL Scholarship](https://www.studyinnl.org/finances/nl-scholarship)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'France Excellence Eiffel Scholarship Program', 'France / French Ministry for Europe and Foreign Affairs', 'France', 'https://www.campusfrance.org/en/france-excellence-eiffel-scholarship-program', 'tuition_only', 'Monthly grant (€1,200 for Master''s programs), international transport assistance, national transport assistance, insurance, housing search assistance, cultural activities. Does not cover tuition fees.', 1284.0, ARRAY['phd','master']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Future foreign decision-makers from the private and public sectors, primarily from emerging countries. Applicants must hold a nationality other than French (dual nationality holders with French nationality are not eligible).', 'Master''s applicants must be under 29 years old. PhD applicants must be under 35 years old. Applications must be submitted by French higher education institutions; students cannot apply directly. Must be admitted to a French higher education institution. Not eligible if already receiving a grant from the French government, Erasmus+, or University Agency of the Francophonie.', '2025-10-01'::date, 'fixed', NULL, NULL, 'France / French Ministry for Europe and Foreign Affairs', 'Master''s, PhD', 'Future foreign decision-makers from the private and public sectors, primarily from emerging countries. Applicants must hold a nationality other than French (dual nationality holders with French nationality are not eligible).', 'Monthly grant (€1,200 for Master''s programs), international transport assistance, national transport assistance, insurance, housing search assistance, cultural activities. Does not cover tuition fees.', 'Not specified, but it is a competitive program.', 'Master''s applicants must be under 29 years old. PhD applicants must be under 35 years old. Applications must be submitted by French higher education institutions; students cannot apply directly. Must be admitted to a French higher education institution. Not eligible if already receiving a grant from the French government, Erasmus+, or University Agency of the Francophonie.', 'Opening of call for applications: October 1, 2025. Deadline for reception of applications by Campus France: January 8, 2026. Sciences Po internal deadline for consideration: October 19, 2025 [5].', '[Campus France - Eiffel Scholarship](https://www.campusfrance.org/en/france-excellence-eiffel-scholarship-program)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'Swedish Institute Scholarships for Global Professionals (SISGP)', 'Sweden / Swedish Institute (SI)', 'Sweden', 'https://si.se/en/apply/scholarships/swedish-institute-scholarships-for-global-professionals/', 'full_ride', 'Full tuition fee coverage, monthly allowance of SEK 12,000 for living expenses, travel grant of SEK 15,000 (SEK 10,000 for scholars from Armenia, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Georgia, Moldova, and Ukraine). Membership in the SI Network for Global Professionals and Sweden Alumni Network.', NULL, ARRAY['master']::text[], NULL, ARRAY['Armenia','Azerbaijan','Bangladesh','Bolivia','Brazil','Colombia','Ecuador','Egypt','Ethiopia','Georgia','Guatemala','Indonesia','Iraq','Jordan','Kenya','Liberia','Malaysia','Mexico','Moldova','Morocco','Nigeria','Peru','Philippines','Rwanda','Senegal','South Africa','Tanzania','Thailand','Uganda','Ukraine','Uzbekistan','Vietnam','Zambia']::text[], 'Citizens of 34 eligible countries (e.g., Armenia, Azerbaijan, Bangladesh, Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, Ecuador, Egypt, Ethiopia, Georgia, Guatemala, Indonesia, Iraq, Jordan, Kenya, Liberia, Malaysia, Mexico, Moldova, Morocco, Nigeria, Peru, Philippines, Rwanda, Senegal, South Africa, Tanzania, Thailand, Uganda, Ukraine, Uzbekistan, Vietnam, Zambia) [6].', 'Citizen of an eligible country, applying for an eligible full-time master''s program at a Swedish university, liable to pay tuition fees, demonstrated work experience, and demonstrated leadership experience. Dual citizenships are allowed, but only one citizenship can be used for application.', '2025-10-16'::date, 'fixed', NULL, NULL, 'Sweden / Swedish Institute (SI)', 'Master''s', 'Citizens of 34 eligible countries (e.g., Armenia, Azerbaijan, Bangladesh, Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, Ecuador, Egypt, Ethiopia, Georgia, Guatemala, Indonesia, Iraq, Jordan, Kenya, Liberia, Malaysia, Mexico, Moldova, Morocco, Nigeria, Peru, Philippines, Rwanda, Senegal, South Africa, Tanzania, Thailand, Uganda, Ukraine, Uzbekistan, Vietnam, Zambia) [6].', 'Full tuition fee coverage, monthly allowance of SEK 12,000 for living expenses, travel grant of SEK 15,000 (SEK 10,000 for scholars from Armenia, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Georgia, Moldova, and Ukraine). Membership in the SI Network for Global Professionals and Sweden Alumni Network.', 'Approximately 200 fully-funded scholarships for master''s studies in 2025 [7].', 'Citizen of an eligible country, applying for an eligible full-time master''s program at a Swedish university, liable to pay tuition fees, demonstrated work experience, and demonstrated leadership experience. Dual citizenships are allowed, but only one citizenship can be used for application.', 'Apply to Swedish master''s programs: October 16, 2025 – January 15, 2026. SI Scholarship application portal: February 9-25, 2026 [6].', '[SI Scholarship for Global Professionals](https://si.se/en/apply/scholarships/swedish-institute-scholarships-for-global-professionals/)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'European Union and European Country Scholarships', 'Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters (EMJM)', 'European Union / European Commission', 'European Union', 'https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/opportunities/individuals/students/erasmus-mundus-joint-masters', 'stipend', 'Full scholarships covering participation costs, travel, visa, and a living allowance.', NULL, ARRAY['master']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Students from all over the world.', 'Bachelor''s degree (first degree) or in the last year of bachelor studies, graduating before the master''s program starts. May also apply with a bachelor''s equivalent level of learning. Students apply directly to the institution running their chosen program.', NULL, 'fixed', NULL, NULL, 'European Union / European Commission', 'Master''s', 'Students from all over the world.', 'Full scholarships covering participation costs, travel, visa, and a living allowance.', 'Not specified, but full scholarships are available for the best-ranked students worldwide. No more than 10% of overall scholarships to students from the same region [8].', 'Bachelor''s degree (first degree) or in the last year of bachelor studies, graduating before the master''s program starts. May also apply with a bachelor''s equivalent level of learning. Students apply directly to the institution running their chosen program.', 'In most cases, applications are submitted between October and January for courses starting the following academic year [9].', '[Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters](https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/opportunities/individuals/students/erasmus-mundus-joint-masters)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'Australian and New Zealand scholarships for developing country students', 'Australia Awards Scholarships', 'Australian Government (Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade - DFAT)', 'Australia', 'https://www.dfat.gov.au/people-to-people/australia-awards/australia-awards-scholarships', 'full_ride', 'Full tuition fees, return air travel, establishment allowance, contribution to living expenses (CLE), Overseas Student Health Cover (OSHC), and more.', NULL, ARRAY['phd','master','bachelor']::text[], NULL, ARRAY['Bangladesh','Bhutan','Cambodia','Indonesia','Laos','Maldives','Mongolia','Myanmar','Nepal','Pakistan','Philippines','Sri Lanka','Timor-Leste','Vietnam','Micronesia','Fiji','Kiribati','Marshall Islands','Nauru','Papua New Guinea','Samoa','Solomon Islands','Tonga','Tuvalu','Vanuatu','Algeria','Angola','Botswana','Egypt','Ethiopia','Ghana','Guinea','Kenya','Madagascar','Malawi','Mauritius','Morocco','Mozambique','Namibia','Nigeria','Rwanda','Senegal','Sierra Leone','South Africa','Tanzania','Gambia','Uganda','Zambia','Zimbabwe']::text[], 'Citizens of participating countries in Asia, the Pacific, Africa, and the Middle East. (Full list: Bangladesh, Bhutan, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Maldives, Mongolia, Myanmar, Nepal, Pakistan, Philippines, Sri Lanka, Timor-Leste, Vietnam, Federated States of Micronesia, Fiji, Kiribati, Marshall Islands, Nauru, Papua New Guinea, Samoa, Solomon Islands, Tonga, Tuvalu, Vanuatu, Wallis and Futuna, Algeria, Angola, Botswana, Côte d''Ivoire, Democratic Republic of Congo, Egypt, Ethiopia, Ghana, Guinea, Kenya, Madagascar, Malawi, Mauritius, Morocco, Mozambique, Namibia, Nigeria, Rwanda, Senegal, Sierra Leone, South Africa, Tanzania, The Gambia, Uganda, Zambia, Zimbabwe, Palestinian Territories)', 'Must be a citizen of a participating country, meet the specific eligibility criteria for your country, not be married to/de facto of a person who holds Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency.', NULL, 'varies', NULL, NULL, 'Australian Government (Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade - DFAT)', 'Undergraduate, Masters, PhD', 'Citizens of participating countries in Asia, the Pacific, Africa, and the Middle East. (Full list: Bangladesh, Bhutan, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Maldives, Mongolia, Myanmar, Nepal, Pakistan, Philippines, Sri Lanka, Timor-Leste, Vietnam, Federated States of Micronesia, Fiji, Kiribati, Marshall Islands, Nauru, Papua New Guinea, Samoa, Solomon Islands, Tonga, Tuvalu, Vanuatu, Wallis and Futuna, Algeria, Angola, Botswana, Côte d''Ivoire, Democratic Republic of Congo, Egypt, Ethiopia, Ghana, Guinea, Kenya, Madagascar, Malawi, Mauritius, Morocco, Mozambique, Namibia, Nigeria, Rwanda, Senegal, Sierra Leone, South Africa, Tanzania, The Gambia, Uganda, Zambia, Zimbabwe, Palestinian Territories)', 'Full tuition fees, return air travel, establishment allowance, contribution to living expenses (CLE), Overseas Student Health Cover (OSHC), and more.', 'Varies by country (thousands globally).', 'Must be a citizen of a participating country, meet the specific eligibility criteria for your country, not be married to/de facto of a person who holds Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency.', 'Varies by country, typically between February and May each year.', '[https://www.dfat.gov.au/people-to-people/australia-awards/australia-awards-scholarships](https://www.dfat.gov.au/people-to-people/australia-awards/australia-awards-scholarships)', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'Australian and New Zealand scholarships for developing country students', 'Manaaki New Zealand Scholarships', 'New Zealand Government (Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade - MFAT)', 'New Zealand', 'https://www.nzscholarships.govt.nz/', 'full_ride', 'Full tuition fees, living allowance, establishment allowance, medical and travel insurance, travel to and from your home country.', NULL, ARRAY['phd','master','bachelor']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Citizens of eligible countries in the Pacific, Asia, Africa, and Latin America.', 'Must be a citizen of an eligible country, meet academic and English language requirements, have at least one year of work experience (or two for some countries).', NULL, 'varies', NULL, NULL, 'New Zealand Government (Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade - MFAT)', 'Undergraduate, Postgraduate (Diploma, Certificate, Masters, PhD)', 'Citizens of eligible countries in the Pacific, Asia, Africa, and Latin America.', 'Full tuition fees, living allowance, establishment allowance, medical and travel insurance, travel to and from your home country.', 'Varies.', 'Must be a citizen of an eligible country, meet academic and English language requirements, have at least one year of work experience (or two for some countries).', 'Varies by country, typically February-March.', '[https://www.nzscholarships.govt.nz/](https://www.nzscholarships.govt.nz/)', TRUE),
