tution, not holding Canadian citizenship/PR, not already receiving GAC or federal granting agency funding, not already enrolled in a Canadian degree program.', 'Canadian institutions had until March 31, 2026, to submit applications for the 2026-2027 academic year. Application period is now closed.', 'https://www.educanada.ca/scholarships-bourses/can/institutions/study-in-canada-sep-etudes-au-canada-pct.aspx?lang=eng', TRUE),
  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'Canadian scholarships and fellowships for developing country students', 'Scholarships and Educational Exchanges for Development – Phase 2 (SEED-2)', 'Government of Canada (Global Affairs Canada)', 'Canada', 'https://www.educanada.ca/scholarships-bourses/can/institutions/seed-bpeed.aspx?lang=eng', 'tuition_only', 'College/Undergraduate: $10,200 for 4 months or $15,900 for 8 months. Graduate: $10,200 for 4 months or $12,700 for 5-6 months. Covers visa/study/work permit fees, airfare, health insurance, living expenses, ground transportation, books and supplies. Tuition fees must be waived by Canadian institutions.', 10200.0, ARRAY['phd','master','bachelor']::text[], NULL, ARRAY['Brunei','Cambodia','Indonesia','Laos','Malaysia','Myanmar','Philippines','Thailand','Timor-Leste','Vietnam','Fiji','Kiribati','Marshall Islands','Micronesia','Nauru','Palau','Papua New Guinea','Samoa','Solomon Islands','Tonga','Tuvalu','Vanuatu','Mongolia']::text[], 'ASEAN Member States (Brunei Darussalam, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, The Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, Timor-Leste, Vietnam); Pacific Island Countries (Cook Islands, Fiji, Kiribati, Marshall Islands, Micronesia, Nauru, Niue, Palau, Papua New Guinea, Samoa, Solomon Islands, Tonga, Tuvalu, Vanuatu); Mongolia.', 'Citizens of eligible countries, enrolled full-time at a post-secondary institution in an eligible country, paying tuition to that institution, not holding Canadian citizenship/PR, not already participating in a Government of Canada funded scholarship, not already enrolled in a Canadian degree program, not a previous SEED recipient. Focus on studies/research contributing to the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development.', '2026-03-24'::date, 'fixed', NULL, NULL, 'Government of Canada (Global Affairs Canada)', 'College/Undergraduate (short-term study or research), Graduate (Masters and PhD) (short-term study or research)', 'ASEAN Member States (Brunei Darussalam, Cambodia, Indonesia