  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'World Bank, IMF, and Multilateral Development Bank Scholarships', 'Japan-IMF Scholarship Program for Asia (JISPA)', 'International Monetary Fund (IMF), funded by the Government of Japan.', 'Global', 'https://www.imf.org/en/countries/resrep/oap-home/jispa-home', 'tuition_only', 'Tuition-related costs and most living expenses, including admission and tuition fees, monthly stipend, allowance for one round-trip economy airfare, orientation program fees (Master’s Track only), pre-arrival allowance (visa fees and medical exam) (Master’s Track only), field-trip fees (Master’s Track only), and research-related fees (Ph.D. Track only).', NULL, ARRAY['phd','master']::text[], NULL, ARRAY['Bangladesh','Bhutan','Cambodia','India','Indonesia','Kazakhstan','Kyrgyzstan','Malaysia','Maldives','Mongolia','Nepal','Papua New Guinea','Philippines','Sri Lanka','Tajikistan','Thailand','Timor-Leste','Turkmenistan','Uzbekistan','Vietnam']::text[], 'Junior government officials from Bangladesh, Bhutan, Cambodia, India, Indonesia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyz Republic, Lao P.D.R., Malaysia, Maldives, Mongolia, Nepal, Pacific Island Countries, Papua New Guinea, Philippines, Sri Lanka, Tajikistan, Thailand, Timor-Leste, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan, and Vietnam.', 'National of one of the specified Asian countries; officials employed and nominated by specific government agencies (e.g., central bank, ministry of finance); holding a Bachelor’s degree for the Master’s Track / a Master’s degree for the Ph.D. Track; fluent in English; for Ph.D. track, applicants must secure admission to a doctoral program in Japan independently; priority given to candidates under 36 years old, who have not obtained a Master’s Degree from outside their own country, and have a minimum of 2 years work experience in the public sector.', NULL, 'annual', NULL, NULL, 'International Monetary Fund (IMF), funded by the Government of Japan.', 'Master’s Track and Ph.D. Track.', 'Junior government officials from Bangl