  ('manus_ai_2026_05_03', 'World Bank, IMF, and Multilateral Development Bank Scholarships', 'Japan Africa Dream Scholarship (JADS) Program', 'African Development Bank (AfDB) and the Government of Japan.', 'Japan', 'https://www.afdb.org/en/about-us/careers/japan-africa-dream-scholarship-jads-program', 'tuition_only', 'Tuition fee coverage (24 months), monthly living stipend (24 months), air travel (home country to host university and back), health insurance. Special grant for research and thesis preparation may be available. Computer literacy, preparatory language, and similar courses may be covered in special circumstances.', NULL, ARRAY['master']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'Citizens of African Development Bank’s regional member countries.', 'Minimum Bachelor’s degree or equivalent in energy, agriculture, health, environmental sustainability, engineering studies or related areas with excellent academic records and relevant professional experience; at least 1 year of paid employment in home country or other African countries after Bachelor’s degree within the past 3 years; 35 years old or younger, and in good health; gain admission to an approved master’s degree course at a Japanese or African partner university; not enrolled in another graduate degree program; must be a citizen of one of the African Development Bank’s regional member countries; not an Executive Director, his/her alternate, and/or staff of all types of appointments of the African Development Bank Group or a close relative.', NULL, 'fixed', NULL, NULL, 'African Development Bank (AfDB) and the Government of Japan.', 'Master’s level.', 'Citizens of African Development Bank’s regional member countries.', 'Tuition fee coverage (24 months), monthly living stipend (24 months), air travel (home country to host university and back), health insurance. Special grant for research and thesis preparation may be available. Computer literacy, preparatory language, and similar courses may be covered in special circumstanc